insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (2, 'Getting started with OvalEdge Data Catalog', '<p>This guide helps you to navigate through various features and functionality of OvalEdge and will guide you to get started with OvalEdge quickly.</p><p><br></p><h2><strong>Basic Navigation</strong><strong><span class="fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable" contenteditable="false" draggable="true"><iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/349670501" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" class="fr-draggable" style="width: 352px; height: 148px;"></iframe></span></strong><br></h2><p>The first step is the user login. Use your username and password to log in. Press on the &#39;Forgot my Password&#39; button to reset your password. Once you log in, you will see a left menu and a top navigation bar.</p><ul><li><strong>Left Menu -&nbsp;</strong>It provides access to various applications within OvalEdge.</li></ul><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="??" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"> <strong>You know that you can press on the right arrow&nbsp;</strong><img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/right-arrow.jpg" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/right-arrow.jpg" style="width: 25px; height: 25px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>to expand and collapse the left menu.</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Top Menu bar -&nbsp;</strong>It is used for searching or using it as a gateway to favorite applications.</li><li><strong>Bookmark -&nbsp;</strong>You can bookmark your favorite application, table&nbsp;or report by navigating to that page and clicking the bookmark icon.</li></ul><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"> <strong>You can pin your favorite bookmarks on the browser header and use it as an extended favorites bar for easy navigation.</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Quick Search Bar -&nbsp;</strong>You can search for any table, column, file&nbsp;or report using the quick search bar. In case the results are not available, you can perform a detailed search using the Smart-Catalog application.</li></ul><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"> <strong>Adding a profile picture is recommended because it provides three times more visibility about you in your company.</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Profile -&nbsp;</strong>This is a basic application for you to update your password, profile picture&nbsp;or phone number.</li><li><strong>Messages -&nbsp;</strong>It displays all of your messages. The messages displayed in bold require your attention the most as they are specifically directed towards you.</li></ul><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"> <strong>You can press a unique identifier to sign in your messages to get to the entire data catalog.</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Dashboard -&nbsp;</strong>It visually provides you all of the insights about your company.</li></ul><p><br></p><h2><strong>Navigate / Research / Explore / Find Data</strong></h2><p><strong><span class="fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable" contenteditable="false" draggable="true"><iframe width="640" height="360" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/351240320" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" class="fr-draggable"></iframe></span></strong><br></p><p><br></p><ul><li><strong>Navigating Data Functionality (Tags)</strong> - Use the tag application to get to the data quickly. Simply keep clicking the subject area you are interested in and keep exploring. Tag applications have a tree structure. Once the data is displayed, you would see the statistics and all the data objects associated with it.</li><li><strong>Navigating/ Research/ Explore Data Technically (Smart Catalog) -&nbsp;</strong>Use Smart Catalog application to navigate to the data using databases, schema, files, reports like Tableau, Power BI reports. You can use various ways to research data. Either you can type the keyword in Explore All or research based on the specifics tabs.&nbsp;<ul><li><strong>Reports</strong> are where you can search all the Tableau, Power BI, or any other kind of reports, charts, etc.</li><li><strong>Data Story</strong> application is the entire knowledge base for your data. You can create a wiki kind of documentation in the data story.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Data Changes</strong> let you explore all the changes in data; using this, you can research the data elements that have changed and compared by date.</li><li><strong>Metadata Changes&nbsp;</strong>lets you understand the latest changes in the metadata. Simply sort by table change date or column change date to understand the change.</li></ul></li></ul><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"> <strong>C</strong><strong>lick on the table to compare the metadata changes.</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Navigating/ Explore Data using Glossary of Terms -&nbsp;</strong>When you implement a glossary of terms, you can also explore data using business terms. Click on Glossary of Terms Application and search your desired business term. When the business term is found, you can read more about the terms, its usage, and all the details and also see its related terms.</li></ul><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"> <strong>You can also view the associated data dictionary.</strong></p><p><br></p><h2><strong>Understanding Data</strong></h2><p><strong><span class="fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable" contenteditable="false" draggable="true"><iframe width="640" height="360" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/351260903" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" class="fr-draggable"></iframe></span></strong><br></p><p>Once you click on a table, file, report, or query, you can see many details about the specific data object and its relationship with other objects. OvalEdge provides much information about a selected object by which you can quickly understand the data using various data statistics. OvalEdge also provides a comprehensive view of all kinds of relationships like references, entity-relationship, pattern relationships, etc.</p><p><img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"> <strong>When you are writing content, you can click on @ sign to add links to other data objects to ask questions.</strong></p><p><img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"> <strong>Whenever you see blue color text or label, this means you can click on it to understand more.</strong></p><p><img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/light_bulb1.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/light_bulb1.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"> <strong>You can reach to help by just hover and click on the question mark.</strong></p><ul dir="ltr"><li><strong>Statistics / Profiled Results -&nbsp;</strong>Profiled results provide a way to understand data quickly, and you can see various stats like the top 50 values, various counts of every field.</li><li><strong>Top Users -</strong> When you have any questions about the data, you can see the insights such as who is the right user who can answer your question.</li><li><strong>Endorsements -</strong> When you are using some report, or table in your analysis, you should endorse that table, so others can see various endorsements.</li><li><strong>Entity Relationships -&nbsp;</strong>Entity relationships are direct relationships between various tables. These relationships are identified by two scores, Similarity Score and Join Score. When the Similarity score is trending towards 100, this means these two tables are duplicates, and when the Join score is trending towards 100, this means that it&#39;s a perfect primary key and foreign key relationship.</li><li><strong>Lineage -&nbsp;</strong>Using the lineage tab, you can understand where the data is coming from and how it is processed and where it&rsquo;s going. OvalEdge also shows the lineage at the column level by clicking the graph, line, or appropriate text between two main objects.</li><li><strong>References -&nbsp;</strong>When the table is used by any other object in documentation, query, it is showing in references.</li></ul><h2><strong>Collect Data specific to your project</strong></h2><p>When you are working on a specific project and want to collect data from the entire organization, you can use the Project application. You can create and share the project with your colleagues. Make a project your default project. Now anywhere in your OvalEdge data catalog, you can click on the Project icon to add the data to your project. You can also add comments specific to your project.&nbsp;This way, all the data objects are assembled in your project.</p><h2><strong>Collaborate / Ask questions about data</strong></h2><p>OvalEdge allows you to ask questions about the data from anyone in the organization. However, you would like to ask a question from either its designated steward, owner, or a user who is using that data object. Using OvalEgde, you can understand the users who are mostly using that data object. It provides three numbers, Views, Queries, and Questions responses.</p><p><img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"><strong>&nbsp;To ask a question, simply click on the user and type your question. You can add more users or data objects by a @ sign.</strong></p><h2><strong>Analyze / Query Data</strong></h2><p>When profiled results are not sufficient to give you detailed information about the data and your data related question is not answered, use the Query Sheet to either build a query or write a query. OvalEdge allows non-SQL users to write SQL using step by step.</p><p><br></p><p><span class="fr-video fr-deletable fr-fvc fr-dvb fr-draggable" contenteditable="false" draggable="true"><iframe title="Query Analysis" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/351275661" width="480" height="270" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="" class="fr-draggable"></iframe></span><br></p><h1><br></h1><h1><strong>Building OvalEdge data catalog</strong></h1><p>This guide is for the users who want to connect OvalEdge to multiple sources and document/catalog the data into OvalEdge so that all the end users can find and explore data with ease.</p><p>The building of the OvalEdge data catalog is done primarily two ways:</p><ul><li>Automatic</li><li>Human curation with AI assistance</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>I. Automatic by various OvalEdge integrations and algorithms:</strong></p><p>OvalEdge has a variety of algorithms to build the data catalog. You would need administrative access to build the data catalog.</p><ul><li><strong>Crawling -&nbsp;</strong>Crawling allows OvalEdge to connect to various applications, databases, data warehouses, data lake, reporting, and visualization technologies. Crawling brings all the metadata like tables, columns, data types from source systems into OvalEdge. Crawling in OvalEdge is as simple as connecting. &nbsp;Use appropriate technology to connect to the database and then click the crawl button to crawl the desired database.</li></ul><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong>To connect the desired database, you may have to add the JDBC jar file, into the OvalEdge jar folder which is configured in configurations.</p><ul><li><strong>Profiling -</strong> Profiling collects various statistics about the data. OvalEdge has pre-built algorithms and queries which execute on the database server. OvalEdge can profile various relational databases, but can not profile visualization software and data lake natively.</li></ul><p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"><strong>&nbsp;</strong>File system like NFS, S3, HDFS does not have the processing power, so OvalEdge uses its proprietary technology to perform the profiling.</p><ul><li><strong>Profiling Controls -</strong> As OvalEdge uses the database&rsquo;s processing power to profile/analyze the data so it may create a certain workload on databases. To control this workload, OvalEdge provides profiling settings. Configure these settings appropriately based on the database server&#39;s processing power and after discussion with DBAs. OvalEdge default settings can be used for playing it safe.</li><li><strong>Relationship Building -&nbsp;</strong>OvalEdge support relationship building via the various mechanism.<ul><li><strong>Relationship via Crawling -&nbsp;</strong>When there are primary, foreign keys are defined in the database; OvalEdge automatically picks as a relationship while crawling.</li><li><strong>Pattern Relationship via Profiling -&nbsp;</strong>When we profile a database, all the relationship which have similar pattern gets identified.</li><li><strong>Relationship building for Hadoop based &nbsp;data lake only -&nbsp;</strong>You can build various relationships using Hadoop based algorithms.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Lineage Building -&nbsp;</strong>OvalEdge has a comprehensive framework to build lineage. Lineage building is performed using the OvalEdge advance job framework. Select the appropriate job to build the lineage.</li></ul><p><br></p><p><strong>II. Human Curation with AI Assistant:</strong></p><p>When data is well organized, it is&nbsp;easy for end-users to navigate and research the data. Use tags application to navigate and organize the data. In the tag application, you can use &quot;+&quot; icon to create new tags and drag the tag to make its child. Use the edit icon for adding a better description and use the Recommendation for an AI-assisted tagging application.</p><h1><br></h1><h1><strong>Security &amp; Data Governance using OvalEdge</strong></h1><p>Administrators can provide access to data and metadata by various roles are permissions and can also assign owners, stewards for various data objects.</p><ul><li><strong>Data Owner&nbsp;</strong>means that they are responsible for controlling the access and writing policies about the data access. They would also be the approver of any workflow request to grant access to data.</li><li><strong>Data Steward&nbsp;</strong>is responsible for managing metadata, business glossary, and assigned data objects. They would also be the approver of any changes in the metadata and tags.</li><li><strong>Roles</strong> may be a business function or group of people require certain data access. A user can be part of multiple roles.</li><li><strong>Permissions&nbsp;</strong>are the type of access any data object will have to a given role. OvalEdge has multiple kinds of permissions.<ul><li><strong>Meta Read</strong> makes data accessible and lets you read the metadata and descriptions.</li><li><strong>Meta Write</strong> lets you update various descriptions.</li><li><strong>Data No Access&nbsp;</strong>means that although they can see the metadata but can not view the data.</li><li><strong>Data Preview</strong> means that the user can view the data, can see profiled results but can not download or query the data.</li><li><strong>Data Read</strong> allows the user to view as well as download and query the data.</li><li><strong>Data Write</strong> allows the user to edit or update the data. In order to provide the Data Write access, the service account of that database must have Data write permissions.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Admin</strong> allows providing access to others via workflow. <strong>OE_ADMIN</strong> is the global administrator and allows users to configure the security and every possible function in OvalEdge.</li><li><strong>A domain</strong> is a high-level function of any organization. Generally, the Site, Business Unit are domains.</li><li><strong>Data Asset Group (DAG)</strong> is a group of Data Assets. Any table, file, or report must belong to a DAG. The assignment of the owner, steward, and security groups is at the DAG level. By default, all the tables belong to a schema; reports belong to Info Groups and files belong to a folder. Schema, report group, and folder are also DAG. &nbsp;You can also create a DAG Tag so that you can change the default behavior of the table/file/reports to the DAG tag level.</li><li><strong>Glossary of terms</strong> is an application where all the business terms can be maintained. In OvalEdge these terms are also a tag and can be applied to a table or field so that it becomes a data dictionary.</li></ul><p><img draggable="false" class="emoji fr-fil fr-dib" alt="" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"><strong>&nbsp;You can load these terms from an excel file.&nbsp;</strong></p><p><br></p>', 'gettingstarted', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (3, 'What is OvalEdge Data Catalog?', '<p><strong>Data catalog</strong></p><p dir="ltr">OvalEdge &nbsp;Data catalog is an advanced search engine. It allows data users to search and locate all the contents of database objects quickly.&nbsp;</p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-f6147e01-7fff-5174-7c14-3a8c1386558e"><img style="width: 20px; height: 20px;" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/light_bulb1.png" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/light_bulb1.png" class="fr-fil fr-dib">&nbsp;</b><strong>Need to find a particular database object but not sure how to search?</strong></p><p><br></p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">Databases</b></p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">What is the purpose of the schema search?</b></p><p dir="ltr">This page displays a list of all the databases and schemas crawled from your Organization. The databases and schemas you see change your search and the filter criteria. You can filter and customize your search results to find what you want. The &quot;Reset&quot; button clears all the filters applied to this page and restores it to its original listings.</p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-7a86189f-7fff-4ecd-36b7-3e5f16a12e8b"><img style="width: 20px; height: 20px;" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/warning%20icon.jpg" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/warning icon.jpg" class="fr-fil fr-dib"></b><strong>&nbsp;Filtering your search results change your search settings in other data catalog tabs.</strong></p><p><br></p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">Tables</b></p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">What is a table search?</b></p><p dir="ltr">Table search is designed to make a local search on individual tables and populate the results based on the search. Similar to the Schema search page, this has various filters that can be used to narrow down your search results.&nbsp;</p><p dir="ltr">A smart search in data tables provides the following abilities:</p><p dir="ltr"><em><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">P</b><strong>artial word matching&nbsp;</strong>-&nbsp;</em>Parts of words can be matched to get the result</p><p dir="ltr"><em><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">M</b><strong><em>at</em>ch the words in any order -&nbsp;</strong></em>Regardless of the order or position they appear in the table</p><p dir="ltr"><em><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">P</b><strong>reserved text -&nbsp;</strong></em>Provides ability to search for an exact phrase</p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68"><em>Case insensitive&nbsp;</em>-&nbsp;</b>Users can use upper or lower case letters.</p><p dir="ltr"><br></p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-2ffc883c-7fff-ae75-050c-fdd2c21e8730"><img style="width: 20px; height: 20px;" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/stop%20and%20note.png" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/stop and note.png" class="fr-fil fr-dib"></b><strong>&nbsp;Do you know? OvalEdge enhances the user search experience with unique scores such as&nbsp;Popularity, Importance, Null density, and Density score.</strong></p><p><br></p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">Files</b></p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">How to search a File?&nbsp;</b></p><p dir="ltr">OvalEdge stores your files in a file system. The file search page displays only the cataloged files. File search allows the user to search for specific files and view their data content and the file statistics. The page also provides an option to download the file to the user directory outside the application.</p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-ebabf4ad-7fff-078d-172b-4f73e5bf96aa"><img style="width: 20px; height: 20px;" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" class="fr-fil fr-dib"></b><strong>&nbsp;OvalEdge supports the following file systems:</strong></p><p dir="ltr"><strong>Comma Separated Value (.csv),&nbsp;Microsoft Excel (.xlsx, .xls), Optimized Row Columnar (.orc),&nbsp;</strong><strong>Simple JSON, Nested JSON,&nbsp;XML, Parquet, AVRO</strong></p><p><br></p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">Queries</b></p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">What is a Query Search?</b></p><p dir="ltr">In addition to the text search, the query search engine allows OvalEdge users to search through all the saved queries from the entire data lake. Queries that are written on a data table get specific results and make the databases more usable.</p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-070277b4-7fff-bf28-3b15-816967eaae73"><img style="width: 20px; height: 20px;" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/stop%20and%20note.png" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/stop and note.png" class="fr-fil fr-dib"></b><strong>&nbsp;Do you know? We&nbsp;can write a new query from the Query search page&nbsp;just by selecting any query item,&nbsp;then clicking the nine dots&nbsp;</strong><img src="oecss/images/helpcenter/ninedots1.png" id="photo-id" style="width: 34px; height: 32px;" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/ninedots1.png" class="fr-fil fr-dib"><strong>&nbsp;icon and select &quot;Add New Query&quot;.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p><p><br></p><p dir="ltr"><strong>Reports</strong></p><p dir="ltr"><b id="docs-internal-guid-bd9fcad7-7fff-f0a9-de3b-ba4ba84a7c68">How to search for Reports?</b></p><p dir="ltr">Report view is a single page that lists all the reports&nbsp;and dashboards created using OvalEdge and other visualization tools.&nbsp;</p><p dir="ltr"><strong>Report</strong> search allows users to search for a particular report or dashboard stored in the entire ecosystem. A user can perform a search by selecting a specific chart name if known or filter all the contents within a specific report&nbsp;group.</p><p dir="ltr"><br></p>', 'datacatalog', true, '', '', 'admin', now());
