insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (4, 'What is a Database Summary Page?', '<p><strong>What is the&nbsp;database&nbsp;Summary Page</strong>?</p><p><!--{cke_protected}%3Cmeta%20charset%3D%22utf-8%22%20%2F%3E--></p><p dir="ltr"><style type="text/css"><!--{cke_protected}{C}%3C!%2D%2Dtd%20%7Bborder%3A%201px%20solid%20%23ccc%3B%7Dbr%20%7Bmso-data-placement%3Asame-cell%3B%7D%2D%2D%3E--></style>A database schema is a structure that represents the entire database. <em><strong>Summary Page </strong></em>makes it easier for OvalEdge users to go through the list of database objects quickly and find relevant information. It has a content editing space&nbsp;that allows users to write, describe, and edit the business descriptions&nbsp;related to a data object.<br><br><!--{cke_protected}%3Cmeta%20charset%3D%22utf-8%22%20%2F%3E--><b id="docs-internal-guid-1a117e8d-7fff-a224-cfc0-4237c957852a"><img data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/light_bulb1.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/light_bulb1.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></b><strong>&nbsp;Want to know when the business description was last updated and by whom?&nbsp;Click the history <img src="oecss/images/helpcenter/history.png" id="photo-id" style="width: 25px; height: 25px;" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/history.png">&nbsp;icon to see the&nbsp;changes in the data object content over a time period.</strong><br><br>The descriptive statistics listed in the tabular format and the data object-specific statistics gives users a better understanding of the quality of the data. Top users display&nbsp;user interaction details. It helps other users learn from people with more experience in that data element. The User review window helps users in an organization to trust the data object and to approve its content through endorsements. Databases, tables, and table columns can be added directly to the user projects for cumulative and easy access by clicking the icon. Tags and Terms can be added directly to databases to organize them functionally.<br><br><!--{cke_protected}%3Cmeta%20charset%3D%22utf-8%22%20%2F%3E--><b id="docs-internal-guid-b54779e4-7fff-f271-61ad-d9d14ea856a6"><img data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 20px; height: 20px;"></b><strong>&nbsp;The user has to profile the data objects(databases/ tables/ tablecolumns/ files/ filecolumns) to collect the statistics. </strong></p>', 'schema', true, '', '', 'admin', now());
