insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (20004, 'What are tags and methods of tagging?', '<p><style type="text/css"><!--{cke_protected}{C}%3C!%2D%2Dtd%20%7Bborder%3A%201px%20solid%20%23ccc%3B%7Dbr%20%7Bmso-data-placement%3Asame-cell%3B%7D%2D%2D%3E--></style>Tags are the keywords that allow users to easily organize the data and categorize them to improve data search and quick discovery. OvalEdge tags help users to explore their data elements with a single click.<br>OvalEdge provides both a controlled tagging method (where user selects from existing tags that other users have created) and a free tagging method (where a user can create a new tag). Tags are added to data objects like databases, tables, table columns, files, file columns, reports, report columns, business glossary, data stories, and queries. Each data object can have a single tag or multiple tags. Also, each tag can have multiple data objects.<br><b id="docs-internal-guid-3516c9ac-7fff-2b4c-e5ac-f53474601891"><img data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 25px; height: 25px;"></b><strong>&nbsp;Tags are typically used in searches and with other features to give&nbsp;more control and power to search within OvalEdge. </strong></p><p><b id="docs-internal-guid-3516c9ac-7fff-2b4c-e5ac-f53474601891"><img data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="width: 25px; height: 25px;">&nbsp;User&nbsp;role&nbsp;needs to be configured to create DAG Tags and Custom Tags.</b></p><p><br></p>', 'schema.tags', true, '', '', 'admin', now());
