t-family: "Helvetica Neue", sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;''>Delete Role - Admin can delete any role by clicking on the delete icon.</span></span></span></li></ol><p><span style=''font-size: 14px; font-family: "Helvetica Neue", sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;''>Based on the above information provided, role will be defined.</span></p>', 'ad.createuserrole', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (36201, 'What are the different Metadata permissions that affect meta data access ?', '<p style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><strong>META READ</strong> or <strong>META WRITE</strong> access applies a level of security on metadata so that end-users have limited access to data objects.&nbsp;</span></span><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">Meta Permissions by itself does not grant access to data. Data access depends on data permissions.</span></span></p><p style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><strong>META READ</strong> should be able to <strong>ONLY VIEW</strong>&nbsp;the metadata of all the data objects like Database, Tables, Files, Reports, Columns, Queries,Tags, Terms and,&nbsp; Custom Fields.</span></span></p><p style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;"><strong>META WRITE</strong> Permissions should be able to <strong>VIEW</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>UPDATE</strong>&nbsp;all the data objects metadata like Database, Business Description, Tables, Tags, Terms and, Additional Fields.</span></span></p><p style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;">A consolidated list of Meta Permissions is displayed below.</span></span></p><p style="margin:0in"><br></p><div><table valign="top" style="border-collapse:collapse; border-style:solid; border-color:#a3a3a3; border-width:1pt; border:undefined" title="" summary="" class=" cke_show_border"><tbody><tr><td style="border-style:solid; border-color:#a3a3a3; border-width:1pt; vertical-align:top; width:3.452in; padding:4pt 4pt 4pt 4pt"><p style="margin:0in"><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="font-famil