atically chosen while creating domain terms."}'' style="font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); position: static;">iation preferences for each Domain. The selected preferences are automatically chosen while creating domain terms.</span></span></span></p><p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">User have following preferences while creating domain terms:</span></span></span></p><ul><li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">Copy title to catalogue :&nbsp;</span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">Before publishing a term, users can select this option to replace the associated object title with the term name.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></li><li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; position: static;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">Copy business description to the catalogue :&nbsp;</span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">Before publishing a term, users can select this option to replace the associated object description with the term description.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></li><li><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">Restricted:&nbsp;</span><span style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">Users can restrict the data column, the data in the total column of the selected table goes invisible.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></li><li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 8pt; position: static;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">Masked:</span><span style="background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">&nbsp;Users can mask the data column. The content in the column is hidden but the column is still visible.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></li><li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 12pt; position: static;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="font-family: Roboto,sans-serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">Show Classification at dictionary:</span><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;">&nbsp;Before a term is published, users can add classifications to the terms.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></li></ul><p><span style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; position: static;"><img data-fr-image-pasted="true" src="https://helpcenter.ovaledge.net/oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" data-cke-saved-src="oecss/images/helpcenter/pointer_hand.png" style="box-sizing: border-box; border-width: 0px; border-style: solid; border-color: currentcolor; max-width: 100%; height: 20px; cursor: pointer; padding: 0px 1px; text-align: left; width: 20px;" class="fr-fil fr-dib"> Select the classification according to the term definition and the sensitivity of the data.</span></p>', 'bg.dataassociations', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (38024, 'How to configure search keywords?', '<p><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">The&nbsp;</span><span data-sheets-userformat=''{"2":15167,"3":{"1":0},"4":{"1":2,"2":65280},"5":{"1":[{"1":2,"2":0,"5":{"1":2,"2":0}},{"1":0,"2":0,"3":3},{"1":1,"2":0,"4":1}]},"6":{"1":[{"1":2,"2":0,"5":{"1":2,"2":0}},{"1":0,"2":0,"3":3},{"1":1,"2":0,"4":1}]},"7":{"1":[{"1":2,"2":0,"5":{"1":2,"2":0}},{"1":0,"2":0,"3":3},{"1":1,"2":0,"4":1}]},"8":{"1":[{"1":2,"2":0,"5":{"1":2,"2":0}},{"1":0,"2":0,"3":3},{"1":1,"2":0,"4":1}]},"11":4,"12":0,"14":{"1":2,"2":16711680},"15":"Arial","16":11}'' data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Existing Elastic Search functionality is enhanced with the configuration of keywords and user id. When the user searches and view, the score will be recorded as 1, and if the user configures it, score will be recorded as 3. Here any user can add a keyword and the Meta-Write users can mark the keyword as Enable/Disable. It won''t allow adding duplicate Keywords.&quot;}" style="font-size: 14px; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); position: static;">Elastic Search functionality is enhanced with the configuration of user-defined search keywords. When the user searches and view, the score will be recorded as 1, and if the user configures it, score will be recorded as 3. Any other user can also vote the keywords by using Thumb symbol and score count will be increase by 1.</span></p>', 'bg.confsearchkey', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (40001, 'What is a data asset group tag?', '<p>Data Asset Group tag is responsible for organizing and maintaining the security, ownership, and control of similar data assets grouped such as database schemas, tables, and reports.<br></p>', 'hp.dataassetgroups', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (40003, 'What are non assignable Tags?', '<p>If a tag is marked as Non Assignable, the tag will not be available to be associated to any data object. You can mark any parent or a child tag as a non assignable tag.</p>', 'sp.nonassignabletag', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (40004, 'What is the purpose of adding tag here in Homepage?', '<p><span data-sheets-userformat=''{"2":15165,"3":{"1":0},"5":{"1":[{"1":2,"2":0,"5":[null,2,0]},{"1":0,"2":0,"3":3},{"1":1,"2":0,"4":1}]},"6":{"1":[{"1":2,"2":0,"5":[null,2,0]},{"1":0,"2":0,"3":3},{"1":1,"2":0,"4":1}]},"7":{"1":[{"1":2,"2":0,"5":[null,2,0]},{"1":0,"2":0,"3":3},{"1":1,"2":0,"4":1}]},"8":{"1":[{"1":2,"2":0,"5":[null,2,0]},{"1":0,"2":0,"3":3},{"1":1,"2":0,"4":1}]},"11":4,"12":0,"14":[null,2,16711680],"15":"Arial","16":12}'' data-sheets-value=''{"1":2,"2":"Tagging allows users to categorize the data and organize them functionally which makes it easier to find.\r"}'' style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); position: static;">Tagging allows users to categorize the data and organize them functionally which makes it easier to find. </span> </p>', 'hp.addtag', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (41000, 'What happens when you enable the metadata notification?', '<p>You can enable this&nbsp;to receive notifications whenever the data objects in the watchlist undergo a metadata change.To trigger the metadata change notification, the source should be recrawled.<br></p>', 'watch.metadata', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (41001, 'What happens when you enable the data notification?', '<p>You can choose to receive notifications whenever the data objects in the watchlist undergo a significant percentage of data change.To trigger the data change notification, the source should be reprofiled.<br></p>', 'watch.data', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (41002, 'Who is a Owner?', '<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif">An Owner is a user who has complete access to a data object like a Database, Table, File, Report group, and responsible for managing its&nbsp;permissions. The permissions and access can be managed either at the technical(data objects )&nbsp;or functional level(Domain).<br>&nbsp;</span></span></span><i><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif"><span style="color:black">This tab displays the data objects for which the user is responsible as an Owner.</span></span></span></span></i></p>', 'at.udowner', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (41003, 'Who is a Steward?', '<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif">Steward is a Data Quality expert who is in charge of ensuring the quality of both the actual business data and the corresponding metadata. Data stewards have the responsibility to approve any content change request on data objects like Tables/Columns/Files/Reports/Business Glossary term.&nbsp;<br>The content changes are generally the business descriptions, associated tags, and terms.<br>When a user raises a content change request on tables/columns/files/reports, the <strong>STEWARD</strong> of that data object gets notifications through email to approve the request. When a user raises a content change request on a business glossary term, the <strong>STEWARD</strong> of the domain gets a notification.</span></span></span><br></p><p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif"> </span></span></span><i><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif">This tab displays the data objects for which the user is responsible as a Steward.</span></span></span></i></p>', 'at.udsteward', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (41004, 'Who is an Author?', '<p style="margin:0in 0in 8pt; text-align:justify;"><span style="font-size:12pt;"><span style="line-height:107%;"><span style="font-family: Roboto, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;"><span style="color: black;">Is one who contributes to the data content like business description for tables, files, reports and also contribute to data stories.</span></span></span></span></p><p><em><span style="font-size: 14px;"><span style="line-height: 107%; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">This tab displays the data objects for which user is responsible as an Author.</span></span></em></p>', 'at.udauthor', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (41005, 'What is OvalEdge Access?', '<p><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif"><span style="color:black">This tab lists all the meta and data permissions on the data objects that a user is assigned access using OvalEdge application. </span></span></span></span>&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;&#8203;<br></p>', 'at.access', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (41006, 'What is Remote Access?', '<p><span style="font-size:12.0pt"><span style="line-height:107%"><span style="font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif"><span style="color:black">This tab lists all the meta and data permissions on the data objects that a user is assigned&nbsp;in the&nbsp;remote application(data source).</span></span></span></span></p>', 'at.remoteaccess', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


insert into helpcenter_topic(topicid, description, content, context, active, type, external_link, createdby, createdate) values (41007, 'How do you receive the ticket notification in Email?', '<p><style type="text/css"><!--{cke_protected}{C}%3C!%2D%2Dtd%20%7Bborder%3A%201px%20solid%20%23ccc%3B%7Dbr%20%7Bmso-data-placement%3Asame-cell%3B%7D%2D%2D%3E--></style>OvalEdge allows users to select if they would like to receive an email notification, regarding these actions.&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Collaboration (When mentioned by @ within the OvalEdge application)</li><li>Watchlist Alerts</li><li>System Alerts&nbsp;<br></li></ul><p>On choosing the notification a user can get an email notification from the following modules:</p><ul><li>Projects</li><li>Crawler</li><li>Job Workflow</li><li>Business Glossary</li><li>User Notification</li><li>Collaboration</li></ul>', 'mr.emailnotification', true, '', '', 'admin', now());


